<br>
I disagree completely.<br>
<br>
All of those things that you charge are going to pull in powergamers are also going to pull in roleplayers.  There is an immense feeling of cooperation in the game, as opposed to the continued levels of competition that EQ fosters.  EQ continues to force you to choose between gaming or roleplaying, while the lack of stress from the cooperative environment in DAoC actual fosters roleplaying.<br>
<br>
I have hope for this server, and I hope that most of the powergamers will grow tired of the restrictions here.  However, my hope and my expectations are not the same.  The same basic problems of the game remain: competition, seperation, item-obsession, restrictions and large amounts of wasted time.  Removing those hurdles does not help just gamers.  <br>
<br>
In actuality, the 'gamers' care less about those hurdles than most roleplayers.  But taking those problems out of the way, or at least limiting them, also limits the amount of stress in the game, and I have seen stress impact roleplayers to a much greater degree than it impacts griefers, doodz, and powergamers.<br>
<br>
As I said, I hope the environment here is enough to foster a less stressful environment, and in turn I hope that FV is a server that restores the players ability to overcome the problems in EQ so that we can spend more time in character.  But those hurdles being removed in DAoC actually allow for that environment naturally, without a constant battle by roleplayers to avoid falling into the pitfall of sacrificing roleplaying for gaming. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urazzlerdazzler.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Razzlerdazzler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/11/01 9:07:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why RPers are frustrated with Powergamers.</span><hr size=1> All youre servers are now belong to us! <p><img src="http://1johnny.freeservers.com/Razzler.jpg" border="0">
